Sure, here are 10 random parts that can be created in Autodesk Inventor:

1. Gearbox casing
2. Bicycle frame
3. Industrial robot arm
4. Kitchen faucet
5. Handheld vacuum cleaner
6. Drone frame
7. Medical device enclosure
8. Automotive engine block
9. High-pressure pump housing
10. Solar panel mounting bracket

These are just a few examples of the diverse range of parts that can be designed and manufactured using Autodesk Inventor. The software is highly versatile and can be used to create parts for a wide variety of industries, from automotive to aerospace, consumer products to industrial equipment.
